thread.title: Liberty soccer's Alicia Chambers picks good time for 2nd varsity goal
thread.title_full: Liberty soccer's Alicia Chambers picks good time for 2nd varsity goal

title: Liberty soccer's Alicia Chambers picks good time for 2nd varsity goal
text:
Liberty freshman defender Alicia Chambers entered Thursday night's game against Freedom with only one career varsity goal. 
Chambers picked a great time for No. 2. 
She knocked in a goal following a header from Olivia Askerneese to give Liberty a 2-1 lead with 36:30 left in the second half. 
It helped the Hurricanes get the 3-2 win over Freedom at a soggy Bethlehem Area School District Stadium. 
"It's a really good feeling," Chambers said. "I just love soccer. It's my happy place." 
RELATED: Liberty's Cailey Sanchez gets best of childhood soccer coach 
Chambers, who also scored against Dieruff on Sept. 26, started the season coming off the bench but now has found a spot in the starting lineup. 
"I'm kind of nervous but I've gotten used to it," Chambers said about playing varsity as a freshman. 
The victory improved the Hurricanes' record to 7-5 on the season. Chambers hopes it can help them get closer to where they want to be at the end of the season. 
"Our goals are to make league and district playoffs. This is going to help us," Chambers said.
